content.raw:
This PR makes pipelines compile again, so I think it's ready to go. The test failures show the following:

~~~
33: [libprotobuf ERROR google/protobuf/descriptor_database.cc:57] File already exists in database: ignition/msgs/time.proto
33: [libprotobuf FATAL google/protobuf/descriptor.cc:1164] CHECK failed: generated_database_->Add(encoded_file_descriptor, size):
33: terminate called after throwing an instance of 'google::protobuf::FatalException'
~~~

I'm not sure why, but it may be related to installing `msgs3` and `msgs4` side-by-side.
